# rca-holistic

## The skill's one commitment

> **An RCA is the mental model the reader inherits.** It succeeds when the
> reader can explain the system from first principles, predict outcomes they
> have not seen, and defend the evidence chain — not when they can list facts.

Three terms with distinct meanings; do not conflate them:

- **inherited mental model** — what lives in the reader's brain after they
  finish the document. The deliverable.
- **mental-model map** — the reader-facing table of takeaways and
  first-principles patterns each level installs. The artifact.
- **evidence path** — the dependency chain L1→L2→…→L12 plus L11 replay probes.
  The composition rule.

NEVER make the RCA reader learn internal skill terms such as "level schema".
The agent may use schema thinking internally; the RCA should present mental
handles in ordinary language.

The mental-model map is the unit of work. Everything else (12 levels, story arc,
claim classification, command-rationale pairing, freshness probes, adversarial
gates) is one of three things:

- A *production rule* — how to build the mental model (per-level dimensions;
  see `references/holistic-ladder.md`).
- A *quality gate* — whether the mental model is useful: plain-language
  takeaway, first-principles pattern, incident relevance, and transfer value.
- A *transfer rule* — how the model reaches the reader: table of contents,
  local evidence keys, vocabulary continuity, explicit inversion, and teaching
  prose around tables and diagrams.

The lenses an agent is tempted to treat as separate disciplines are different
views of the same mental-model work. The reader-facing explanation is canonical;
internal scaffolding is only an aid.

## Golden end-state: a capability-transfer trace (behavioral-trace substrate)

This skill's PRIMARY substrate is **behavioral-trace** — perfect completion is
not the four `output/` files as objects; it is a *demonstrated behavior graded
on a reader*. The RCA succeeds only when a zero-context reader, after reading
the package, can perform the six capabilities of the RCA Knowledge Contract:
draw the boundaries, trace the mechanism, recreate the investigation cold,
reject the false explanations, repair/rollback safely, and decide what toil to
remove. The ceiling surface is therefore **capability-transfer**, not mechanical
parse-clean — a package whose validators all pass but whose reader cannot
predict an unseen outcome has FAILED this skill.

This is a falsifiable, delete-an-element-loses-a-prediction trace:

| Reader capability the package installs | The element that carries it | What the reader loses if that element is deleted |
|---|---|---|
| Draw the affected system boundaries | L2 repo rigor table + L3 runtime topology diagram | Cannot predict which other components share the failure boundary |
| Trace trigger → symptom → failed invariant | L4 code/data flow + the anti-log causal spine | Falls back to log-order recall; cannot transfer the mechanism to a nearby incident |
| Recreate the investigation from cold | L11 command playbook with the six-part probe-rationale per command | Has commands but not the authority model; cannot choose the equivalent probe in a different stack |
| Reject the main false explanations | Explicit inversions (X3) + the Evidence Ledger A1/A2/A3 labels | Inherits conclusions on trust; cannot defend them under adversarial questioning |
| Repair or roll back safely | `how-to-fix.md` mechanism → state-plane → rollback boundary → verification probe | Copies a patch without knowing which invariant it closes or how to prove convergence |
| Decide what toil to remove vs keep manual | `sre-toil-removal-proposal.md` evidence-bound recommendations | Automates bad work at machine speed, or adds a longer checklist instead of removing judgment from the hot path |

The **NEAR-MISS this skill MUST reject** is the *decorative trace*: a package
that recites all twelve levels, renders every diagram, passes
`validate-rca-completeness.sh`, and still leaves the reader unable to predict an
outcome they have not seen — facts rearranged into prettier headings with no
transferable mental model. Mechanical receipts are the FLOOR; the reader's
demonstrated capability is the CEILING. Because that reader is a live human, the
final capability grade is **PROVISIONAL** until a real zero-context reader
exercises the package; the golden specimen
(`examples/01-mfrr-activation-crashloop/`) is the recorded fixture standing in
for that judge, and the adversarial gate (Phase 5) is the surrogate
capability-transfer probe. See `skill-design.md` for the full golden
end-state declaration and `verification/adversarial-receipts.md` for the recorded review.

## Enforcement Contract

Every MUST, NEVER, and BLOCKED in this skill is binding. Gates and checklists
are not advisory — an unsatisfied gate means the downstream step is BLOCKED,
not deferred. Soft language (should, consider, try to, ideally) appears only
in rationale and commentary, never in instructions. If this document says MUST,
it means MUST.


## Human-Comprehension Contract [CRITICAL]

The RCA is written for a **human engineer to read and learn from**, not for one
agent to hand evidence to another. Rigor and evidence discipline stay intact;
the *register* changes. These rules are binding and machine-checked.

**1. Evidence codes NEVER appear in the narrative.** `A1`/`A2`/`A3`, `E8`-style
probe IDs, and internal reviewer names (`socrates`, `el-demoledor`, …) are audit
metadata. They live in the **Evidence Ledger**, evidence/Context table columns,
the Mutation log, or fenced blocks — NEVER bare in a narrative sentence. The
reader must not have to learn the document's code system to understand the
incident. The prose states the same status in human words:

| Status | NEVER in prose | Required human phrasing |
|---|---|---|
| FACT (directly observed) | `[A1, E8]` | "The live Azure metrics showed…", "The repository history showed…", "The provider documentation states…" |
| INFER (reasoned) | `A2 inference` | "This is an inference from the measured size and the partition behavior, because…" |
| UNVERIFIED (blocked) | `[A3]` | "This remains unverified because the job history was not read; the next probe would be…" |

`scripts/validate-rca-completeness.sh` G20 fails any narrative prose carrying a
bare code or reviewer name. The full audit trail stays in the ledger — reachable
by an auditor, invisible to a reader who just wants to learn.

**Conservation of evidence (MUST).** Moving a code out of prose means RELOCATING
it to the ledger, NEVER deleting it. Every per-claim source reference the prose
carried (file:line, probe/command/`E`-codes, commit/PR/build IDs) MUST still
appear in the Evidence Ledger, an evidence table column, or the Evidence index.
G20 only checks that codes are *absent from prose* — it cannot check they are
*present in the ledger*, so the cheapest way to pass G20 is to delete the audit
trail. That is a rigor regression masquerading as a register change. The
adversarial gate (Phase 5) MUST verify relocation: every classified claim in the
final RCA traces to a specific, replayable probe in the ledger, exactly as the
inherited evidence did.

**2. Open with a human Executive summary** (MUST, G24). Before the Context Ledger
and the levels, a `## Executive summary` section explains the incident in plain
but rigorous prose — what happened, what system was involved and how it works at
a high level, the visible symptom, the actual cause, the impact (operational
impact, distinct from the alert that fired), what is not yet verified, why the
alert fired (the mechanism, not "the alert fired"), why the proposed fix is the
right fix, and what a future engineer should remember. Lead with the SYSTEM in
human terms, never with resource IDs and arrow-chains.

**3. Every diagram teaches a mechanism** (MUST, G25). Each diagram is wrapped:
an intro sentence before (what you'll see + the question it answers), then prose
after that READS the picture — what am I looking at, which parts communicate,
what flows, where the bottleneck/failure point is, why this shape produces the
symptom, what changes if one part behaved differently — then the one mental model
to keep and the connection to the prior section. Diagrams must be COMPLEMENTARY
(topology, runtime/burst flow, failure mechanism, feedback loop, timeline,
decision tree), never the same idea redrawn. After an architecture diagram, lead
with the failure PATH and the mechanism; push the fact-list into a table.

**4. First principles before symptom.** Define the real mechanics before
interpreting the alert: what the metric measures, why the limit exists, how
rejection/throttling happens, how retries distort the observed counts, why a
utilization gauge is not impact, why a count is not a rate, why an alert can be
correct yet poorly calibrated, why a system can be "not down" but still degraded,
and why the remediation follows from the mechanism.

**5. Report, explanation, and teaching are distinct layers.** The RCA is not a
pile of correct facts; it is a coherent explanation. Deliver, in order: the
human Executive summary → the system model (prose-first, mechanism) → the failure
mechanism (the causal chain) → the Evidence Ledger (where codes live) → the
impact assessment (operational impact vs alert symptom) → the fix strategy (why
this order) → the learning. The twelve levels supply the audited depth beneath
that spine.

**Human-Comprehension Gate** (run before `status: complete`; revise on any NO):
would a human understand this without decoding labels? · does the opening explain
in human prose? · are codes isolated in the ledger? · does every diagram teach
and connect? · are first principles before conclusions? · are facts/inferences/
unknowns clear without a code in every sentence? · does the reader know
what/why/how-we-know/what-next? · does it REDUCE cognitive load, or transfer
decoding onto the reader? The mechanical parts (G20 label-leak, G24 opening, G25
diagram-prose) are validator-enforced; the "reads agent-to-agent" judgment is for
the Phase-5 adversarial gate.

## RCA Knowledge Contract

Every standard RCA starts with an **RCA Knowledge Contract**. The contract is
not an abstract promise that "the reader understands the incident." It is a
falsifiable set of reader capabilities, written with observable verbs and
adapted to SRE/platform troubleshooting:

```text
After reading this RCA package, a zero-context reader can:
1. draw the affected system boundaries and delivery/runtime surfaces;
2. trace the causal mechanism from trigger to symptom to failed invariant;
3. reproduce the investigation from cold using the included probes;
4. reject the main false explanations and explain why they fail;
5. repair or roll back the system safely, with verification probes;
6. identify which toil should be automated, removed, or deliberately left manual.
```

Build the package **backward** from that contract:

```text
RCA Knowledge Contract
        |
        v
Reader capabilities
        |
        v
Knowledge domains -> primitives -> visuals -> probes -> evidence
        |
        v
rca.md + how-to-fix.md + how-to-recreate-this-rca.md
        + sre-toil-removal-proposal.md
```

If a contract line has no knowledge domain, visual/evidence surface, replay
probe, challenge, or sibling-document section that makes it true, the line is
not yet a contract. It is aspiration. Fix the derivation before drafting prose.

### Mandatory Knowledge Domain Map

Before the narrative ladder, name the knowledge domains/aspects that structure
the RCA. A reader with zero context must be able to see what worlds they are
about to learn and why each one matters.

Minimum domains for SRE/platform incidents:

| Domain / aspect | Reader capability it supports |
|---|---|
| Business or functional role | Explain why the failure matters and who is affected. |
| Repo/artifact system | Identify which code/config/IaC owners can change the outcome. |
| Runtime topology | Draw the deployed components, state planes, and failure boundary. |
| Application/data/control flow | Trace how the symptom emerges inside the service. |
| Declarative infrastructure | Compare intended state with actual runtime state. |
| Delivery pipeline | Explain how source becomes runtime, including approvals and gaps. |
| Timeline and latency | Use time as evidence without turning the RCA into a log. |
| Fix mechanism | Connect repair steps to the violated invariant. |
| Verification and falsifiers | Prove the fix by rerunning the failing probes. |
| Reproduction path | Let another human or agent recreate the RCA from cold. |
| On-call recognition | Detect the same class quickly next time. |
| SRE toil removal | Decide what to automate, remove, simplify, alert on, or leave manual. |

The domain map is the RCA's table of epistemic contents. It is not optional
background, and it is not a glossary. Each row must connect to a contract item

