455:    "summary": "Azure App Configuration access failures on MC dev split cleanly by HTTP status AND caller. STATUS: 401 = authentication failed (no/invalid/expired/wrong-tenant Entra token, or a deleted/stale/mis-signed access key); 403 = authorization (missing App Configuration Data role) OR network (application/problem+json type ip-address-rejected / nsp-rejected); timeout = off-VNet. These are mutually exclusive: a missing role is 403 not 401; a blocked VPN is 403/timeout not 401. CALLER: 'the FFs cannot be set' hides THREE callers with three credentials \u2014 (i) interactive user from AVD (your own Entra token), (ii) the FF-apply ADO Terraform pipeline SP eneco-vpp-mc-dev (its Entra token; needs App Configuration Data Owner, granted via group sg-vpp-core-release-masters), (iii) the running FBE/VPP pod reading flags (an access-key connection string from KV secret connectionstrings-app-config via Eneco.Vpp.Configuration.AzureAppConfiguration .Connect(connectionString)). Same status from a different caller = different fix. 'I can see the flags in the portal' is control-plane (ARM Reader) visibility, NOT proof the data-plane call authenticates (and the portal blade can itself 401 on a private-endpoint store in Edge). The store is public_network_access=Disabled + private-endpoint-only ('everything through AVD'); never open public access. Strongest base-rate cause for 'FFs not set' on a slot = the manual approval-gated App Config pipeline never ran/approved (same filer Duncan, FBE Kidu, 2025-09), which predicts NO real 401.",
456:    "root_cause": "Two distinct App Config data-plane code paths (access-key connection-string READ; Entra-SP WRITE via the ADO Terraform pipeline) plus three possible callers plus a control-plane portal view independent of both. Conflating the paths/callers, or treating a rusty filer's paraphrased '401' as a captured status line, routes the fix to the wrong layer. The 18-Jun VPN-timeout ticket (resolved by-design: private endpoint, use AVD) is a DIFFERENT layer from a 401-on-AVD.",
457:    "fix": "Capture the EXACT status + WWW-Authenticate/problem+json body + WHICH caller before acting (it is AVD-gated). 401 Bearer (you) -> az login refresh to the dev-mc tenant; 401 Bearer (pipeline SP) -> rotate the eneco-vpp-mc-dev ADO service-connection secret (NOT a personal login); 401 HMAC (FBE pod) -> check live disableLocalAuth, then re-run the App Config IaC pipeline so Terraform rewrites connectionstrings-app-config (a manual 'az keyvault secret set' on that IaC-managed secret DRIFTS and is silently reverted by the next apply; if unavoidable use a READ key, non-empty guard, --file/stdin not --value, capture prior value); 403 no body -> grant least data role: a DIRECT App Configuration Data Reader for a read, Data Owner via the IaC group ONLY for the apply SP (never add a reader to sg-vpp-core-release-masters \u2014 it is store-wide Data Owner + release-master authority); 403 problem+json -> use AVD / link private DNS, never enable public network access; no error -> approve+run the FF pipeline. 'az role assignment list' is a control-plane read needing ARM Reader \u2014 a command error there is not 'no role'. Verify by EFFECT (failing op returns 200 / slot reads flag), never exit code or portal view. Member of the LL-006 credential/access class.",
