493:    "summary": "An Azure Key Vault certificate is a composite of cert+key+SECRET sharing one name. If a certificate is imported (e.g. by hand) with the same name as a Terraform-managed azurerm_key_vault_secret, the cert's backing secret 'captures' it and `terraform destroy` fails with 403 SecretManagedByKeyVault ('delete the corresponding certificate'). FBE thor stuck-deletion run 1.",
