   106	}
   107	```
   108	
   109	- The store **name embeds a random suffix**; the keeper is stable per slot, so the suffix is stable **within a Terraform state** but **regenerates when the state is destroyed and rebuilt** (delete `2629` `terraform destroy` → create `2412`) → **new store name + new HMAC keys** (name change on `azurerm_app_configuration` is ForceNew) `A2`.
   110	- The browser is handed the **primary _write_ key** connection string `A1` — a security smell (read/write key exposed to the client; orthogonal to the 401 but worth fixing alongside).
   111	- Module output currently exposes only `app_configuration_primary_write_key_connection_string` (`Eneco.Infrastructure/terraform/modules/appconfig/output.tf`) `A1` — a read-only-key hardening needs a new module output.
   112	
   113	**Truth 2 — what Azure actually holds (live 2026-07-19, sub `7b1ba02e-…`, RG `rg-vpp-app-sb-401`):**
   114	Stores that EXIST: `vpp-appconfig-fbe-{boltz-tec, ishtar-xql, jupiter-vlt, kidu-gqk, thor-ubn, veku-xsy}` `A1`.
   115	
   116	**Truth 3 — what the running pods serve (live 2026-07-19):** see L7 drift table. 5 of 7 pods serve connection strings for stores that are **GONE** from Azure `A1`.
   117	
   118	## L6 — The pipeline and how it actually runs
   119	
   120	Create pipeline `azure-pipelines-featurebr-env.yml` stage order `A1` (from source): `DeployInfra` (Terraform writes the KV secret) → `keyvaultandappconfigentries` → `DeployServices` → `DeployFBEInArgoCD` (commits `feature-branch-environments/{slot}.yaml`, triggers ArgoCD, then a **blind 180 s sleep**). **First-create ordering is correct** — the ArgoCD trigger transitively depends on the KV write, so a brand-new slot's first pod bakes the correct credential `A2`. The delete pipeline `azure-pipeline-fbe-del.yml` runs `isTerraformDestroy: true` `A1`. The gap is **recurrence**: on a slot **re-create** (or any operation that recreates the store), the store gets a new name+keys, `application-secret` is updated by CSI, but the **already-running frontend pod is never rolled** (no manifest diff, no Reloader, blind sleep ≠ restart) `A2`. ApplicationSet uses a git generator with automated prune+selfHeal and **no sync-wave** `A1`.
   121	
   122	## L7 — Timeline (live reproduction, 2026-07-19)
   123	
   124	Frozen-snapshot drift test — running pod's BAKED `appconfig.js` store vs current `application-secret` store (SHA-256 compared; secrets never printed) `A1`:
   125	
   126	| slot | pod started | restarts | BAKED store (in pod) | CURRENT store (secret/Azure) | drift | baked store exists in Azure? |
   127	|------|-------------|----------|----------------------|------------------------------|-------|------------------------------|
   128	| boltz  | 2026-07-08 | 0 | `…-boltz-qzz`  | `…-boltz-tec`  | **DRIFT** | **GONE** |
   129	| ishtar | 2026-07-13 | 0 | `…-ishtar-oyn` | `…-ishtar-xql` | **DRIFT** | **GONE** |
   130	| kidu   | 2026-07-16 | 0 | `…-kidu-dfm`   | `…-kidu-gqk`   | **DRIFT** | **GONE** |
   131	| thor   | 2026-07-16 | 0 | `…-thor-dyf`   | `…-thor-ubn`   | **DRIFT** | **GONE** |
   132	| veku   | 2026-07-17 | 0 | `…-veku-ckg`   | `…-veku-xsy`   | **DRIFT** | **GONE** |
   133	| jupiter| 2026-07-07 | 0 | `…-jupiter-vlt`| `…-jupiter-vlt`| match | exists (healthy) |
   134	
   135	All drifted pods have `restarts=0` → they still hold the credential baked at their creation date, while `application-secret` (kept current by CSI rotation, 2 s) has moved to a newer store `A1`. HTTP discriminator (unauth `GET /kv`) `A1`: a **live** store returns `HTTP 401 www-authenticate: HMAC-SHA256` (Duncan's exact symptom); a **deleted** store does not resolve (`HTTP=000`). The precise per-slot recreation count/time is `A3 [blocked: only current store systemData.createdAt readable; store history not retained]` — but the consequence (frozen pod vs live store) is `A1` on every drifted slot.
   136	
   137	## L8 — Fix
   138	
   139	See **[how-to-fix.md](./how-to-fix.md)** for exact edits, commands, and risks. In brief, ranked:
   140	
   141	1. **Immediate mitigation (no code):** `kubectl -n <slot> rollout restart deploy/frontend` re-bakes `appconfig.js` from the now-current secret → 200. Applies to the 5 currently-drifted slots. *This is the manual step Duncan wants removed — used here only as the interim mitigation.*
   142	2. **Primary permanent fix (recommended, no new cluster dependency):** in the FBE create/recreate pipeline, after ArgoCD converges, replace the blind 180 s sleep with `kubectl -n <slot> rollout status deploy/frontend` **+ `kubectl -n <slot> rollout restart deploy/frontend`** so a reused slot's surviving pod is rolled after the final store is in place.
   143	3. **Robustness (trigger-agnostic):** install Stakater Reloader in the Sandbox cluster and annotate the frontend Deployment `secret.reloader.stakater.com/reload: "application-secret"`. Because CSI rotation keeps `application-secret` current (**proven live**: drifted pods' secret already holds the new store), Reloader will roll the frontend automatically on any store/key change.
   144	4. **Strategic root fix:** make `appconfig.js` dynamic — serve the credential from the CSI-mounted `/mnt/secrets-store/connectionstrings-app-config` at request/container-start time instead of a one-shot emptyDir snapshot, eliminating the frozen-snapshot class.
   145	5. **Security hardening (orthogonal, recommended):** hand the browser a **read-only** App Config key instead of the primary **write** key (add a `primary_read_key` output to the appconfig module and reference it in `app-config.tf`).
   146	
   147	## L9 — Verification
   148	
   149	Close on the **observed effect**, never a return code (H-EFFECT-1). After any fix:
   150	
   151	- `kubectl -n <slot> exec deploy/frontend -c frontend -- cat /etc/nginx/html/appconfig/appconfig.js` → the `Endpoint=` host **matches** the live store in `application-secret` and in Azure `A1`.
   152	- Browser DevTools on `https://<slot>.dev.vpp.eneco.com/`: `.appconfig.featureflag/*` returns **200** and the **"Tennet NL"** indicator renders `A1` (filer's DoD).
   153	- Regression: recreate a throwaway slot end-to-end and confirm the frontend serves the correct credential **without** a manual pod delete.
   154	
   155	## L10 — Lessons
   156	
   157	- **A build-time-once artifact must not carry a mutable credential without a refresh trigger.** `appconfig.js` snapshots a value that rotates on infra recreate; the emptyDir + init-once + no-Reloader + healthz-only probe together guarantee the pod cannot self-correct.
   158	- **Out-of-band credentials are invisible to GitOps.** ArgoCD reconciles the manifest, not the CSI-injected secret, so a store recreate leaves the pod "Synced" yet broken. CSI rotation refreshes the *secret* but never the *consumer* that read it once.
   159	- **Green pipeline ≠ runtime health.** A green FBE-create and a `Ready` pod both coexist with a 401.
   160	- The Jun-2026 RCA framed this as a *transient, self-resolving* provisioning window and shipped **no permanent fix**; this incident is the **permanent variant** (store recreate on slot reuse) that recurs until the refresh gap is closed.
   161	- **Fleet check is cheap and high-signal:** comparing each pod's baked `appconfig.js` endpoint to its `application-secret` endpoint surfaces every stale slot in seconds.
   162	
   163	## L11 — End-to-end command playbook (from cold)
   164	
   165	```bash
   166	# 0. Reach the FBE cluster (Sandbox AKS — directly reachable, not AVD-gated)
   167	kubectl config use-context vpp-aks01-d
   168	
   169	# 1. Which slots exist
   170	kubectl get ns | grep -Ev 'kube-|monitoring|system|default|argocd|csi|cert-|mongo|rabbit'
   171	
   172	# 2. Frozen-snapshot drift test (baked appconfig.js vs current application-secret)
   173	for ns in $(kubectl get deploy -A -l app.kubernetes.io/name=frontend \
   174	      -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.namespace}{"\n"}{end}' | sort -u); do
   175	  pod=$(kubectl -n "$ns" get pod -l app.kubernetes.io/name=frontend -o jsonpath='{.items[0].metadata.name}')
   176	  baked=$(kubectl -n "$ns" exec "$pod" -c frontend -- cat /etc/nginx/html/appconfig/appconfig.js \
   177	          | grep -oE 'Endpoint=https://[^;\"]+')
   178	  sec=$(kubectl -n "$ns" get secret application-secret -o jsonpath='{.data.connectionstrings_appconfig}' \
   179	          | base64 -d | grep -oE 'Endpoint=https://[^;\"]+')
   180	  [ "$baked" = "$sec" ] && echo "$ns match" || echo "$ns DRIFT baked=$baked current=$sec"
   181	done
   182	
   183	# 3. Confirm the baked store is gone in Azure (Sandbox sub, read-only)
   184	az resource list -g rg-vpp-app-sb-401 \
   185	  --resource-type Microsoft.AppConfiguration/configurationStores \
   186	  --subscription 7b1ba02e-bac6-4c45-83a0-7f0d3104922e --query "[].name" -o tsv
   187	
   188	# 4. Interim mitigation (re-bakes appconfig.js) — restores 200
   189	kubectl -n <slot> rollout restart deploy/frontend
   190	kubectl -n <slot> rollout status  deploy/frontend
   191	
   192	# 5. Verify EFFECT (not exit code)
   193	kubectl -n <slot> exec deploy/frontend -c frontend -- cat /etc/nginx/html/appconfig/appconfig.js   # endpoint == live store
   194	# then browser DevTools: .appconfig.featureflag/* == 200 and "Tennet NL" visible
   195	```
   196	
   197	## L12 — One-page on-call playbook (5-minute triage)
   198	
   199	- **Symptom:** new/recreated FBE → frontend feature-flag calls 401; **no** Dutch flag / "Tennet NL"; a pod delete fixes it.
   200	- **Confirm in 60 s:** `kubectl -n <slot> exec deploy/frontend -c frontend -- cat /etc/nginx/html/appconfig/appconfig.js` and compare its `Endpoint=` host to `kubectl -n <slot> get secret application-secret -o jsonpath='{.data.connectionstrings_appconfig}' | base64 -d`. **Mismatch = [REDACTED] bug.**
   201	- **Immediate fix:** `kubectl -n <slot> rollout restart deploy/frontend` → re-check the endpoint matches → browser 200.
   202	- **Do NOT:** rotate App Config keys, re-run App Config Terraform, grant Data roles, or touch dev-mc `vpp-applicationconfig-d` — the store/key are fine; the **pod** is stale.
   203	- **Permanent fix owner:** see how-to-fix.md (pipeline rollout-restart ± Reloader ± read-only key).
