    10	
    11	All probes run 2026-07-19 by the coordinator against live Sandbox AKS `vpp-aks01-d`
    12	(kube-context `vpp-aks01-d`, authinfo `clusterUser_rg-vpp-app-sb-401`) and the Sandbox
    13	subscription `7b1ba02e-bac6-4c45-83a0-7f0d3104922e`. Secrets redacted throughout.
    14	
    15	## A1 — the browser→App Config credential chain (frontend pod)
    16	
    17	- Frontend Deployment `frontend` (Helm chart `frontend-0.4.2`, ArgoCD tracking-id
    18	  `<slot>_frontend`) has init container **`init-myservice`** whose sole command is:
    19	  `echo window.VUE_APP_AZ_CONFIG_CONNECTION_STRING = [REDACTED] > /etc/nginx/html/appconfig/appconfig.js`
    20	- `connectionstrings_appconfig` env ← `secretKeyRef{name: [REDACTED] key: connectionstrings_appconfig}`
    21	  (same on init AND main container).
    22	- `appconfig.js` is written into volume **`mydir` (emptyDir: {})** mounted at `/etc/nginx/html/appconfig`
    23	  → frozen once at pod start; regenerated ONLY on pod (re)start.
    24	- Live read of `jupiter` pod `frontend-7db976fcb-g8sbw`:
    25	  `window.VUE_APP_AZ_CONFIG_CONNECTION_STRING = [REDACTED]`
    26	- CSI `SecretProviderClass secret-provider-kv` (provider=azure, keyVault=`vpp-fbe-jupiter-vlt`)
    27	  `secretObjects` maps KV `connectionstrings-app-config` → K8s `application-secret[connectionstrings_appconfig]`.
    28	- Browser SPA calls App Config data plane `/.appconfig.featureflag/*` over **HMAC** — `401 = credential`,
    29	  not RBAC 403, not network 403.
    30	
    31	## A1 — NO refresh mechanism exists
    32	
    33	- `podAnnotations: {}` (chart default) and none set in `VPP-Configuration/Helm/frontend/sandbox/values.yaml`
    34	  → **no `reloader.stakater.com/*` annotation, no config-checksum annotation.**
    35	- Stakater Reloader controller: **absent** cluster-wide (`kubectl get deploy -A | grep -i reload` → none;
    36	  repo grep for `stakater`/`reloader.stakater.com` → no results).
    37	- Frontend `readinessProbe`/`livenessProbe` = `httpGet /healthz` only → a pod serving a dead credential
    38	  still reports **Ready** (probe does not validate App Config).
    39	- CSI secrets-store driver (ns `csi`) args: **`--enable-secret-rotation=true --rotation-poll-interval=2s`**
    40	  → the driver keeps `application-secret` current, but rotation NEVER re-runs the init container
    41	  (init-once + emptyDir), so `appconfig.js` stays frozen.
    42	
    43	## A1 — FROZEN-SNAPSHOT DRIFT reproduced live across the fleet (2026-07-19)
    44	
    45	Per-slot comparison of the running pod's BAKED `appconfig.js` endpoint vs the CURRENT
    46	`application-secret` endpoint (SHA-256 of the full connection string; secret bytes never printed):
    47	
    48	| slot | pod started | restarts | BAKED store (frozen in pod) | CURRENT store (secret/KV) | drift |
    49	|------|-------------|----------|-----------------------------|---------------------------|-------|
    50	| boltz  | 2026-07-08 | 0 | `vpp-appconfig-fbe-boltz-qzz`  | `vpp-appconfig-fbe-boltz-tec`  | **DRIFT** |
    51	| ishtar | 2026-07-13 | 0 | `vpp-appconfig-fbe-ishtar-oyn` | `vpp-appconfig-fbe-ishtar-xql` | **DRIFT** |
    52	| kidu   | 2026-07-16 | 0 | `vpp-appconfig-fbe-kidu-dfm`   | `vpp-appconfig-fbe-kidu-gqk`   | **DRIFT** |
    53	| thor   | 2026-07-16 | 0 | `vpp-appconfig-fbe-thor-dyf`   | `vpp-appconfig-fbe-thor-ubn`   | **DRIFT** |
    54	| veku   | 2026-07-17 | 0 | `vpp-appconfig-fbe-veku-ckg`   | `vpp-appconfig-fbe-veku-xsy`   | **DRIFT** |
    55	| jupiter| 2026-07-07 | 0 | `vpp-appconfig-fbe-jupiter-vlt`| `vpp-appconfig-fbe-jupiter-vlt`| match (healthy) |
    56	
    57	All drifted pods have `restarts=0` → they still hold the ORIGINAL baked credential;
    58	`application-secret` has since moved to a newer store. **5 of 7 active FBE slots are, at the time
    59	of investigation, serving a stale credential** and would show Duncan's 401 / missing-Tennet-NL symptom
    60	until their frontend pod is restarted.
    61	
    62	## A1 — the baked stores are GONE from Azure (proves the failure)
    63	
    64	`az resource list -g rg-vpp-app-sb-401 --resource-type Microsoft.AppConfiguration/configurationStores
    65	--subscription 7b1ba02e-...`:
    66	
    67	- EXIST (live): `vpp-appconfig-fbe-{boltz-tec, ishtar-xql, jupiter-vlt, kidu-gqk, thor-ubn, veku-xsy}`
    68	- GONE (baked into pods, deleted): `vpp-appconfig-fbe-{boltz-qzz, ishtar-oyn, kidu-dfm, thor-dyf, veku-ckg}`
    69	
    70	## A1 — HTTP behaviour discriminates the two surface variants
    71	
    72	Unauthenticated `GET https://<store>/kv?api-version=1.0`:
    73	
    74	- LIVE store (`…boltz-tec`, `…jupiter-vlt`) → DNS `appconfigservice-production-westeurope.trafficmanager.net`,
    75	  **HTTP 401 `www-authenticate: HMAC-SHA256`** ← exactly Duncan's reported symptom (store exists, credential rejected).
    76	- DELETED store (`…boltz-qzz`) → does not resolve, `HTTP=000` (connection fails).
    77	
    78	→ Duncan's clean **401** corresponds to the variant where the pod presents a stale/rotated HMAC
    79	credential to a store that still resolves (rotated keys / brief store overlap). The aged-fleet variant
    80	(store fully deleted) surfaces as a connection error. **Same root cause, two timing variants.**
    81	
    82	## A1 — Terraform: why store identity changes (`VPP - Infrastructure/terraform/fbe/`)
    83	
    84	- `app-config.tf`:
    85	  - `app_configuration_name = format("%s-appconfig-fbe-%s-%s", var.project-prefix, var.environment, random_string.random.result)`
    86	  - `key_vault_secret_name = "connectionstrings-app-config"`,
    87	    `key_vault_secret_value = module.appconfig.app_configuration_primary_write_key_connection_string`
    88	    → the browser is handed the **primary WRITE key** (security smell).
    89	- `common.tf`: `random_string.random` length=3, `keepers = { id = "<prefix>-random-fbe-<environment>" }`
    90	  (environment = slot). Keeper is stable per slot → suffix is stable WITHIN a Terraform state;
    91	  it regenerates only when the slot's state is torn down and rebuilt (**delete pipeline `2629`
    92	  `terraform destroy` → create `2412`**), producing a **new store name + new HMAC keys** (ForceNew).
    93	- appconfig module `Eneco.Infrastructure/terraform/modules/appconfig/output.tf` currently exposes ONLY
    94	  `app_configuration_primary_write_key_connection_string` (→ `azurerm_app_configuration…primary_write_key[0].connection_string`).
    95	
    96	## A1 — Pipeline ordering (from GitOps source extract, sidecar gitops-pipeline-source-extract.md)
    97	
    98	- Create pipeline `azure-pipelines-featurebr-env.yml`: `DeployInfra` (TF writes KV secret) →
    99	  `keyvaultandappconfigentries` → `DeployServices` → `DeployFBEInArgoCD` (commits `{slot}.yaml`,
   100	  triggers ArgoCD, then a **blind 180s sleep**). First-create ordering is CORRECT.
   101	- The credential reaches the pod out-of-band (TF→KV→CSI→secret→init→emptyDir), so it is **invisible to
   102	  the Deployment manifest ArgoCD reconciles** → on a store recreate ArgoCD sees no diff → **never rolls
   103	  the frontend pod** → frozen appconfig.js.
   104	- ApplicationSet `VPP.GitOps/argocd-configuration/applicationsets/vpp-feature-branch-environments.yaml`
   105	  (git generator, automated prune+selfHeal, no sync-wave).
   106	
   107	## Fix-target files (all pulled to latest 2026-07-19)
   108	
   109	- Frontend chart template: `Myriad - VPP/azure-pipeline/Helm/frontend/templates/deployment.yaml` (chart 0.4.2)
   110	- FBE frontend env values: `VPP-Configuration/Helm/frontend/sandbox/values.yaml`
   111	- FBE App Config TF: `VPP - Infrastructure/terraform/fbe/app-config.tf` (+ module output in `Eneco.Infrastructure/terraform/modules/appconfig/output.tf`)
   112	- FBE create pipeline: `Myriad - VPP/.../azure-pipelines-featurebr-env.yml`
   113	- Reloader install (if chosen): `VPP.GitOps` ArgoCD application
   114	
   115	## Precedent / prior knowledge
   116	
   117	- Jun-2026 RCA `log/.../2026_june/2026_06_22_003_feature_flags_fbe_duncan/rca.md`: same symptom, framed as
   118	  TRANSIENT provisioning-window that SELF-RESOLVED on pod rebuild; **no permanent fix shipped**; left open
   119	  "why the credential was rejected while the store key was valid." This RCA closes that gap.
   120	- Vault `fbe-failure-modes-catalog.md` F22: documents the transient variant; fix of record "wait for rebuild";
   121	  no permanent fix documented → the permanent fix here is net-new engineering.

