39:# RCA — Jupiter FBE feature flags fail with 401 on Azure App Configuration (RESOLVED)
40-
41-> **Status: `complete` — RESOLVED 2026-06-26. Root cause confirmed by live probe of the running FBE and
42:> by Duncan's own browser capture (401 → 200 on the `.appconfig.featureflag/*` calls).**
43->
44:> **CORRECTION — read this before the L1–L12 body.** The body below analyzes the **dev-mc shared store
45-> `vpp-applicationconfig-d`**. That was the wrong target. Direct probing of the live Jupiter FBE in the
46:> **Sandbox** AKS cluster (`vpp-aks01-d`, RG `rg-vpp-app-sb-401`) on 2026-06-26 established:
47->
48:> 1. **The Jupiter FBE reads its OWN per-slot store** `vpp-appconfig-fbe-jupiter-qvc.azconfig.io`
49->    (Sandbox), **not** `vpp-applicationconfig-d`. (Resolves the previously-blocked **C17**.) "I can see
50:>    the FFs set properly in the app config" = Duncan was looking at the wrong store (his earlier ticket's
51->    dev-mc URL).
52:> 2. **The failing caller is the browser SPA.** The frontend init container injects the store's connection
53->    string into a browser-served file — `window.VUE_APP_AZ_CONFIG_CONNECTION_STRING` in
54:>    `/etc/nginx/html/appconfig/appconfig.js` — and the SPA calls `…/.appconfig.featureflag%2F*` directly
55:>    over **HMAC**. Duncan's screenshot shows exactly those requests, now 200.
56:> 3. **The store and key were healthy the whole time** (`disableLocalAuth=false`, keys present, CORS `*`,
57->    and the FBE's exact connection string returns 200 + real flags). So the leading dev-mc hypotheses —
58:>    H0 pipeline approval, H1/H1-SP token, H2 key disabled, H3 RBAC — are **refuted/irrelevant** for the
59->    real caller. (Resolves the previously-blocked **C16**.)
60:> 4. **Mechanism:** a **provisioning-window credential-freshness** condition. Store created 09:29 UTC,
61:>    flags written 10:03, Duncan tested ~10:49 against a 23-min-old frontend pod; the healthy pod serving
62:>    a valid `appconfig.js` was rebuilt at 20:17 — after which the calls return 200. **Self-resolved.**
63->
64-> Full live-probe evidence + reproduction commands:
65-> `.ai/tasks/2026-06-26-004_enrich-jupiter-fbe-appconfig-probe/findings.md`. The L1–L12 analysis below is
