664-## L12 — One-page on-call playbook
665-
666:**Anchor question: how do I triage "App Config 401 on dev-mc" in five minutes next time?**
667-
668-| Step | Do | Decide |
669-|---|---|---|
670:| 1 | Ask for / capture the **exact status + body** of the failing call | 401 → auth; 403 → role/network; timeout → network |
671:| 2 | Confirm caller is **on AVD** and the store FQDN resolves to a `10.x` IP | If not → it's the earlier *network* issue: use AVD |
672:| 3 | If **401 invalid_token/wrong issuer** → re-`az login` to dev-mc tenant; check `az account show` | Fixed on retry? done |
673:| 4 | If **401 "Invalid Credential"** (key path) → check `disableLocalAuth` live; if rotated, refresh the KV connection-string secret | **Never** disable/regenerate keys to fix — platform-team gate |
674:| 5 | If **403** (no network body) → check Data role on the calling identity; grant **least** role to the *set* identity | **Never** grant a consumer Data Owner reflexively |
675-| 6 | If flag just **missing** (no error) → check the App Configuration pipeline's approval gate | Approve + run |
676-| — | Remember | "I can see it in the portal" = control plane, ≠ data-plane auth |
